Systems Analyst with Ab Initio tools

NY/NJ (Remote)

Fulltime

Roles & Responsibilities:
• Perform application system design throughout the Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC) utilizing multiple development methodologies including Waterfall, Agile and Iterative; validate and ensure that business requirements are thorough, detailed, and concise.
• Manage data in databases using Data Warehousing platforms, including DB2, SQL query, ETL and back-end processing environment;
• Perform business intelligence analysis using Cognos, Tableau and Data Marts, by performing data profiling, data quality analysis, and data analytics; interpret and write source-to-target mappings; ensure that all Systems Analysis (SA) artifacts follow EPMP guidelines and are developed, reviewed and approved;
• Perform data modeling using SQL and Erwin;
• Provide systems expertise to business stakeholders and serve as the SME for applications;
• Perform data profiling, reference data management, governance, and end-to-end data lineage using Ab Initio tools;
• Provide forecasts and detailed estimates for SA activities and artifacts;
• Collaborate with stakeholders to analyze business requirements and current system behavior to create system design specification documentation, including functional specifications, system use cases, mock-ups, and design models; research customer issues and escalate risks/issues appropriately and in a timely manner;
• Test and investigate issues to determine the appropriate resolution;
• Bachelor's degree (or higher) in applied computer science or related field (willing to accept foreign education equivalent) plus seven (7) years of experience in systems analysis, including data analysis, profiling and governance using Ab Initio.
